## Endnotes

1.  The ASER survey is conducted by Pratham, a non-governmental organization working in the field of education.
2.  The survey covers 70 out of 71 districts in Uttar Pradesh. The district of Shamli was not covered due to logistical constraints.
3.  The learning assessments are based on the National Curriculum Framework (NCF) 2005.
4.  The data is weighted to account for the sampling design.
5.  The confidence intervals are calculated at the 95% level.

